latestPosts.caption:
If you have the chance to do it, do it.

We’re truly soaking up every single moment of our parental leave here, embracing the slow life and quality time together. This time has been an absolute dream come true, allowing us to connect as a new family in a way we never imagined possible. We’ve collected countless cherished memories, from her first splash in the Mediterranean to quiet evenings watching the sunset together, building a foundation of family moments we’ll look back on forever.

I know opportunities like this don’t come around for everyone, and we feel incredibly lucky and privileged to have experienced it. But if the universe aligns, and you ever get the chance to take an extended parental leave abroad, especially somewhere that encourages a relaxed pace of life, this is your sign to do it. The unique memories you’ll make, the deeper bond you’ll strengthen with your little one, and the chance to truly slow down and just be together are truly priceless.
